It's a slap in the face to rippers, uploaders and seeders, like me, for you to criticize without  verifying things or reading up on something you do not know about.

Two channel stereo is chosen for people without five speakers. It's very annoying watching five channel audio on two speakers with certain sounds being higher than others. You always end up playing tag with your volume button.

AAC-LC is a superior audio codec simply due to it having better conversion options and sound quality than MP3. AAC is also well-supported on all devices, including some phones. It's basically a high-end audio codec. AC3 lacks playback support and is equal to AAC.

For those who appreciate and support, thanks.

@agk47: YES, you CAN watch partially downloaded files to test its validity. Torrents download in "pieces," and the pieces that get downloaded can be viewed in many media players before the download is even finished. If a piece is missing in the download while watching it, then that section(piece) of the video will be skipped and continue to where the next downloaded piece is.
